<example id="example" otherprops="examples"><title>Examples</title>
      <p>This section contains examples of how the <xmlelement>linktext</xmlelement> element can be
        used.</p>
<fig id="figure-1">
        <title>Link text with key definitions</title>
        <p>See <xref keyref="elements-keydef"/> for an example of <xmlelement>linktext</xmlelement>
          used with key definitions.</p>
      </fig>
<fig id="figure-2">
        <title>Link text in a map</title>
        <p>The following code sample shows a <xmlelement>linktext</xmlelement> element used in a
          relationship table. The generated link from <filepath>maintenance.dita</filepath> to
            <filepath>installation.dita</filepath> will use the specified link text, while the link
          from <filepath>installation.dita</filepath> to <filepath>maintenance.dita</filepath> will
          use link text based on the title of the topic.</p>
        <!--<p>In this context, the link text should be used for any links that are generated to <filepath>installation.dita</filepath>, rather than generating link text based on the title of the topic.</p>-->
        <codeblock>&lt;map>
  &lt;title>Relationship map&lt;/title>
  &lt;reltable>
    &lt;relrow>
      &lt;relcell>
        &lt;topicref href="installation.dita">
          &lt;topicmeta>
            <b>&lt;linktext></b>Initial set-up information<b>&lt;/linktext></b>
          &lt;/topicmeta>
        &lt;/topicref>
      &lt;/relcell>
      &lt;relcell>
        &lt;topicref href="maintenance.dita"/>
      &lt;/relcell>
    &lt;/relrow>
  &lt;/reltable>
&lt;/map></codeblock>
      </fig>
<fig id="figure-3">
        <title>Link text within a topic</title>
        <p>The following code sample shows how a <xmlelement>linktext</xmlelement> element can be
          used within a topic to provide text for a related link to a non-DITA resource:</p>
        <codeblock>&lt;related-links>
  &lt;link href="SQLJ-example.html" format="html" scope="local"&gt;
    <b>&lt;linktext&gt;</b>Accessing relational data with SQLJ<b>&lt;/linktext&gt;</b>
  &lt;/link&gt;
&lt;/related-links></codeblock>
      </fig></example>
